               <head>
                  <title xml:lang="en">The Icelandic Lucidarius</title>; <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>,
       <origDate notBefore="1650" notAfter="1699">s. XVII 1/2</origDate>, <note> An Icelandic
       parchment fragment from the first half of the seventeenth century containing four fragments
       of the Icelandic version of the German didactic dialogue known as <title>Lucidarius</title>.
       This fragment is the oldest extant manuscript of the Icelandic <title>Lucidarius</title>.
       There are two datings of the fragment: Kristian Kålund dated it to the sixteenth century and
       Jón Helgason to the first half of the seventeenth century.</note>
               </head>
               <msContents>
